773d278197e611101501337e6253af9d 1970-01-01 03:00:00 1. Place lentils and kidney beans in a large bowl ,cover with plenty of water. 
2. Soak for at least 2 hours or overnight and drain.
3. Cook lentils, kidney beans, 5 cups water, and salt in a pot over medium heat until tender, stirring occasionally, about 1 hour. 
4. Remove from heat and set aside. 
5. Keep the lentils, kidney beans, and any excess cooking water in the pot.
6. Heat vegetable oil in a saucepan over medium-high heat. 
7. Cook cumin seeds in the hot oil until they begin to pop, 1 to 2 minutes. 
8. Add cardamom pods, cinnamon stick, bay leaves, and cloves, cook until bay leaves turn brown, about 1 minute. 
9. Reduce heat to medium-low, add ginger paste, garlic paste, turmeric, and cayenne pepper, stir to coat.
10. Stir tomato puree into spice mixture, cook over medium heat until slightly reduced, about 5 minutes. Add chili powder, coriander, and butter, cook and stir until butter is melted.
11. Stir lentils, kidney beans and any leftover cooking water into tomato mixture, bring to a boil, reduce heat to low. 
12. Stir fenugreek into lentil mixture. 
13. Cover saucepan and simmer until heated through, stirring occasionally, about 45 minutes. 
14. Add cream and cook until heated through, 2 to 4 minutes.
15. It's ready t eat with Chapati/Naan, enjoy!!!

  • 1 cup lentils
  • ¼ cup dry kidney beans (Optional)
  • Water to cover
  • 5 cups water
  • Salt to taste
  • 2 tablespoons vegetable oil
  • 1 tablespoon cumin seeds
  • 4 cardamom pods
  • 1 cinnamon stick, broken
  • 4 bay leaves
  • 6 whole cloves
  • 1 ½ tablespoons ginger paste
  • 1 ½ tablespoons garlic paste
  • ½ teaspoon ground turmeric
  • 1 pinch cayenne pepper, or more to taste
  • 1 cup canned tomato puree, or more to taste
  • 1 tablespoon chili powder
  • 2 tablespoons ground coriander
  • ¼ cup butter
  • 2 tablespoons dried fenugreek leaves (Optional)
  • ½ cup cream (Optional)
